quran[17]{c,v,t}:
  27,15,"In the past, We gave knowledge to David and Solomon, and they both said, “Praise God, Who has favored us above many of His servants who believe.”"
  27,16,"And Solomon was David’s heir. He said, “O you people, we have been taught the speech of birds, and on us has been bestowed a little of all things. This is indeed grace manifest from God.”"
  27,17,"And before Solomon, marched a legion of the jinn, the humans, and the birds, and they were arranged in ranks"
  27,18,"Then, when they came to a valley of the ants, one of the ants said, “O you ants, get into your habitations, lest Solomon and his legion crush you without knowing it.”"
  27,19,"So he smiled, amused at its speech, and he said, “O my Lord, order me that I may be grateful for Your favors which you have bestowed on me and on my parents, and that I may do righteous deeds that will please You, and admit me, by Your grace, to the ranks of Your righteous servants.”"
  27,20,"And he looked over the birds and he said, “Why do I not see the hoopoe, or is it among the absentees"
  27,21,"“I will certainly punish it with a severe penalty, or cause it to be absent permanently, unless it brings me a clear reason for its absence.”"
  27,22,"But the hoopoe had not gone far. It approached him and said, “I have compassed territory which you have not compassed, and I have come to you from Sheba with certain findings"
  27,23,"“I found there a woman ruling over them and governing them, and she has been provided everything, and she has a magnificent throne"
  27,24,"“I found her and her people worshipping the Sun instead of God. Satan has made their deeds seem pleasing in their eyes which has averted them from the way, so that they can receive no guidance"
  27,25,"“And so that they do not worship God, He Who brings to light what is hidden in the heavens and the earth, and Who knows what you conceal and what you reveal"
  27,26,"“God, there is no god but He, Lord of the Throne Supreme.”"
  27,27,"Solomon said, “Soon will we see whether you have told the truth or lied"
  27,28,"“Go with this letter of mine, and deliver it to them. Then draw back from them, and wait to see what answer they return.”"
  27,29,"The queen said, “O you advisors, here addressed to me is a letter worthy of respect"
  27,30,"“It is from Solomon, and it reads as follows"
  27,31,"“Be not arrogant towards me, but come to me as a Muslim.”"